Anne, I am sorry you are such a cyber Groupie. My mother died about 10 years ago from cancer, after a very long and painfilled 3 years of struggle. I buried her with my brother, with shovels, not the bulldozer the morturary usually used. Seemed to be the right thing to do. Therefore I find your spoof to be incredible tasteless and stupid, and needlessly painful. I know you had know way of knowing that, but when you run with dogs, expect to catch fleas.  <br><br>
As to the rest of you, I will play with as I please, when I please, because I am an American who is not afraid of honest dialogue and the free flow of ideas. Clearly, Tom being the best example, can dish it out but you can't take it.  <br><br>
You all have been calling me names and throwing insults from day one when Cook attacked &quot;the little commie&quot;.  I am fed up with the double standard here, that you all can insult and slur me, but I must take it and be nice.  Every time Cook called me the &quot;little commie&quot; or the &quot;draft dodger&quot; who amoung you spoke up to tell him to stop, or that he was wrong?   No one. NOT ONE OF YOU ON LINE STOOD UP TO HIM FOR ME. I got a lot of b/c mail that agreed with me, but on line, you all let him suck you down into his gutter.  <br><br>
Just like World War II, and the Trials of the Nazi's, silence can get your killed.  Calling me a &quot;draft dodger&quot; is the exactly the same as me calling you guys &quot;baby killers&quot;, and you know my position on that. I never did it and I hated those who did.<br><br>
What is it that makes the vets on this site so blind? So insensitive to others?  Is a protestor not a human being? Does he not bleed or feel?  You were fighting &quot;commies&quot; to perserve the American way, no?  Does that not include the Freedom to Protest and Freedom of Speech?  But..where does it include the Right of Combat Vets to hurt others, just because they were hurt?  The only way evil can spread, it is written, is that good men (and women) stay silent. The Germans demonstrated that in the 20's, 30's and 40's, and now the Viet Nam Vet shows how sensitive they are to the pain of others, that there pain must reigh supreme, that they have the first and only claim to pain.<br><br>
Get in line with the rest of the victims of history, yours in only one of many chapters.
